        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 6 at 12:02AM CDT until May 6 at 1:00AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1202 AM CDT/1102 PM MDT/, a severe thunderstorm was located 15
miles east of Red Bluff Reservoir, or 16 miles north of Mentone,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Jal, Jal Airport, and Bennett.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT/300 AM MDT/ for
southeastern New Mexico...and western Texas.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
